pgTitle: Sit Down, Shut Up (2009 TV series)

rows.text: Acting principal Susan Sezno is threatening to fire one of the teachers of Knob Haven High School due to budget cuts. Meanwhile, Vice Principal Proszakian ingests pills that are suspected to be steroids.

Larry volunteers to give a speech in hopes of impressing Miracle, but Ennis steals Larry's thunder when a YouTube video of Ennis's ranting becomes popular. Meanwhile, Willard becomes a driver's ed teacher so he can overcome his fear of driving and Helen the librarian discovers that Happy the Janitor is keeping the books she was ordered to burn.

Sue crashes her car into Ennis and tries to conceal the accident by hiding him (still stuck halfway through the windshield of her car) in the auto shop class until the school can afford insurance. Later, after almost getting electrocuted while trying to hot-wire the car, Ennis believes that he has become a half-man/half-car superhero named Sedanimal. Stewart takes over the school's failing newspaper in an effort to make enough money to purchase insurance, and turns it into a tabloid.

Sue Sezno ditches the teachers in order to testify in a Senate hearing about why Knob Haven High School is the worst school in the country. In an effort to prevent her from going the staff splits up into teams and they race to stop her. Ennis gets sidetracked as he tries to prove his bravery to his father.

When Larry hears from the Deep South Council of Physical Fitness, he tries to convince Sue to try to get rid of all the junk food, but she refuses since "It's my main profit, besides lotto tickets and cough syrup." Seeing that Sue won't get rid of the junk food, he and "Happy" decide to remove all the junk food from the school to help the kids get fit. Outside Larry starts to throw away the junk food, but unintentionally hits Willard's head in the process.
